# Romanovka, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Romanovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Vitimskoye Rural Settlement, Bauntovsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 1,198 as of 2017. There are 17 streets.
Geography
Romanovka is located in the Vitim Plateau, 171&nbsp;km south of Bagdarin (the district's administrative centre) by road. The P436 regional road connecting Ulan-Ude and  Chita passes through Romanovka across the plateau. Road P437 connecting Romanovka and Bagdarin begins in the town.
